-- U.S. mortgage applications fall in latest week-MBA
-- By Caroline Valetkevitch
-- Wed May 28, 2014 07:00AM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, May 28 (Reuters) - Applications for U.S. home mortgages fell last week as both purchase and refinancing applications declined, an industry group said on Wednesday.

The Mortgage Bankers Association said its seasonally adjusted index of mortgage application activity, which includes both refinancing and home purchase demand, fell 1.2 percent in the week ended May 23. The MBA's seasonally adjusted index of refinancing applications fell 1.4 percent, while the gauge of loan requests for home purchases, a leading indicator of home sales, slipped 1.1 percent.  <^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ U.S. mortgage data: http://link.reuters.com/guv37s ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^> Fixed 30-year mortgage rates averaged 4.31 percent in the week, the lowest level since June 2013. It was down 2 basis points from 4.33 percent the week before.